{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":7},{"title":2,"author":3,"date":4,"citation":5,"uri":6},"Le sculture da Alesa","Portale","2009","\u003Cspan>Elisa Chiara Portale, «Le sculture da Alesa», in \u003Ci>Alaisa-Halaesa. Scavi e ricerche (1970-2007)\u003C/i>, a c. di G. Scibona e G. Tigano (Messina: Sicania, 2009), 67–92\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/BCIMMIKZ",[8,143],{"file":9,"uri":9,"title":10,"status":11,"editionAuthor":13,"type":14,"objectType":18,"material":22,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":27,"handNote":34,"date":57,"places":62,"geo":72,"provenance":64,"provenanceGeo":76,"country":79,"region":80,"settlement":64,"repository":81,"idno":85,"textLang":88,"tmNumber":92,"facsimile":93,"letterHeights":100,"publications":110,"zotero":118,"keywords":126,"html":136,"bibl":137,"citedRangeSort":138,"languageSort":89,"materialSort":23,"typeSort":15},"ISic000804","Dedication of a statue to Ceres, by Iulius Acilius Hermes, sevir",{"_":12},"edited",null,{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},"dedication","#function.dedication","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/88.html",{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},"statue base","#object.statue_base","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.html",{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},"marble (white)","#material.stone.marble","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html","",{"layout":28},{"p":29,"rs":30,"damage":26},"The Latin text is engraved over two lines (letters c.20 mm high, but of uneven height), to a maximum length of 52 cm.",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":35,"dimensions":36}," The letters show some irregularity, with fairly pronounced serifs, and lengthy tails to the letter R. The first two words are separated from the rest by a space; an interpunct is visible at the end of the dedicant’s name, and the final abbreviated phrase is separated from the rest by a large hedera (ivy leaf). The letter I in line 1 is frequently taller than the rest (but so too is the first L in line 1); the final I of line 1 is somewhat irregularly carved.",[37,45,51],{"type":38,"l":39,"from":40,"to":40,"h":41,"unit":42,"atLeast":43,"atMost":44},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","18-25","mm","18","25",{"type":38,"l":46,"from":47,"to":47,"h":48,"unit":42,"atLeast":49,"atMost":50},"Line 2","line2","19-23","19","23",{"type":52,"l":53,"from":40,"to":47,"h":54,"unit":42,"atLeast":55,"atMost":56},"interlinear","Interlineation lines 1-2","7-15","7","15",{"_":58,"notBefore":59,"notAfter":60,"evidence":61},"Statue can be dated stylistically to the late Antonine period (i.e. the 180s or 190s CE), and the text is compatible with such a date.",180,199,"context",[63,67],{"_":64,"type":65,"ref":66},"Halaesa","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462225",{"_":68,"type":69,"ref":70,"offset":71},"Castel di Tusa","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525099","near",[73],[74,75],37.99907,14.26197,[77,78],37.998037,14.262643,"Italy","Sicily",{"_":82,"role":83,"ref":84},"Antiquarium e sito archeologico di Halaesa ","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/053",{"_":86,"type":87},"ME 20194","inventory",{"_":89,"mainLang":90,"languages":91},"Latin","la",[89],"175724",{"n":94,"url":95,"height":96,"width":97,"desc":98,"surfaceType":99},"screen","ISic000804_tiled.tif","1949px","4512px","Photo J. Prag courtesy Soprintendenza BBCCAA di Messina","front",[101,104,107],{"atLeast":102,"atMost":103},18,25,{"atLeast":105,"atMost":106},19,23,{"atLeast":108,"atMost":109},7,15,[111,112,113,114,115,116,117],"L'année épigraphique: revue des publications épigraphiques relatives a l'antiquité romaine., 1888-","Scibona, 1971, Epigraphica Halaesina I","Manganaro, 1988, La Sicilia da Sesto Pompeo a Diocleziano","Scibona, 2008, Statuary","Portale, 2009, Le sculture da Alesa","Prestianni Giallombardo, 2012, Spazio pubblico e memoria civica. Le epigrafi dall'agora di Alesa","Prag, Tigano, 2017, Alesa Archonidea: il lapidarium",[119,120,121,122,123,124,125],"R46KDTZX","UISW82JC","RZSFKACR","EQC3W4UU","BCIMMIKZ","CJISRIUV","MI64NB9L",[127,128,129,15,19,23,130,131,132,133,130,134,135,90],"isic000804","dedication of a statue to ceres, by iulius acilius hermes, sevir",{"_":12},"halaesa","castel di tusa","italy","sicily","antiquarium e sito archeologico di halaesa","latin","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Cereri sacr(um) \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span> Iulius Acilius Her-\u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>mes · pro honor(e) seviratus ❦ d(eae) d(onum) d(edit) \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":138,"ptr":139,"ref":141,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6},"80-87 fig.7",{"target":140},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/BCIMMIKZ",{"_":142,"target":142},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001670",{"file":144,"uri":144,"title":145,"status":146,"editionAuthor":13,"type":147,"objectType":148,"material":151,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":152,"handNote":156,"date":165,"places":169,"geo":172,"provenance":64,"provenanceGeo":174,"country":79,"region":80,"settlement":64,"repository":177,"idno":178,"textLang":180,"tmNumber":182,"facsimile":183,"letterHeights":188,"publications":191,"zotero":195,"keywords":199,"html":203,"bibl":204,"citedRangeSort":205,"languageSort":89,"materialSort":23,"typeSort":15},"ISic000768","Dedication by a sevir to Concordia",{"_":12},{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},{"_":149,"ana":150,"ref":21},"base","#object.base",{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},{"layout":153},{"p":154,"rs":155,"damage":26},"The epigraphic face is preserved for a width of 12.5 cm, with two lines of Latin letters filling the available field.",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},{"lettering":157,"dimensions":158},"The letters are tall, neatly cut and closely spaced (height c.30mm), and words are separated by simple triangular interpuncts. The letters are lightly serifed. E is tall and narrow, T has a curved cross-bar, rising to the right.",[159,162],{"type":38,"l":160,"from":40,"to":47,"h":161,"unit":42,"atLeast":161,"atMost":161},"Line 1-2","30",{"type":52,"l":163,"from":40,"to":47,"h":164,"unit":42},"Interlineation line 1 to 2","?",{"_":166,"notBefore":167,"notAfter":168},"Late 1st century CE, or 2nd century CE",51,200,[170,171],{"_":64,"type":65,"ref":66},{"_":68,"type":69,"ref":70,"offset":71},[173],[74,75],[175,176],37.998047,14.262635,{"_":82,"role":83,"ref":84},{"_":179,"type":87},"ME 20226",{"_":89,"mainLang":90,"languages":181},[89],"175722",{"n":94,"url":184,"height":185,"width":186,"desc":187,"surfaceType":99},"ISic000768_tiled.tif","3395px","7360px","Photo J. Prag, courtesy Soprintendenza di Messina",[189],{"atLeast":190,"atMost":190},30,[111,112,113,192,193,194,115,116,117],"Manganaro, 1989, Iscrizioni Latine nuove e vecchie della Sicilia","Facella, 2006, Alesa Arconidea: ricerche su un'antica città della Sicilia tirrenica","Scibona, 2008, The Epigraphs",[119,120,121,196,197,198,123,124,125],"EZMBJ6GN","J4XWZPV6","6GFVUASD",[200,201,202,15,149,23,130,131,132,133,130,134,135,90],"isic000768","dedication by a sevir to concordia",{"_":12},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>Conco]ṛdiae · Aug[ustae\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ethus · sev[ir\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":20